# Questions to ask the User for Clear the problem.
Check your network connection status.
Check Airplane Mode.
Forget and reconnect to the Wi-Fi.
Restart your modern and wireless routor.
Try to connect to the same network on a different device.
Run network commands.
Disable power saving for Wi-Fi adapter.
Restart your PC.
There are some sites for the question that you should ask the end user.
[The first URL](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/fix-wi-fi-connection-issues-in-windows-9424a1f7-6a3b-65a6-4d78-7f07eee84d2c.)
[The second URL](https://community.spiceworks.com/t/in-help-desk-support-how-do-you-troubleshoot-a-network-internet-issue/195911)
There are three sites with basic network wifi Connection for trouble shooting.
[The first link](https://www.techtarget.com/searchnetworking/tip/Wireless-network-troubleshooting-Connectivity)
[The Second link](https://www.ctctechnologies.com/articles/is-your-business-wi-fi-acting-up-check-these-8-places-first)
[The third link](https://www.highspeedinternet.com/resources/no-internet-connection-troubleshooting-guide)
Two sites with trouble shooting info to the Access point or wi-fi router.
[The first link 1](https://www.networkdatapedia.com/post/acess-point-troubleshooting)
[The second link 2](https://www.dell.com/support/kbdoc/en-ca/000127788/troubleshooting-wireless-networking-issues)
